item.description:
Iterable An iterable is an object that can produce an iterator by calling the iter() function on it. Eg: list, tuple, dict, set, string, etc. It must define the __iter__() method:
__iter__(): method called on the initialization of an Iterator. (eg. by iter()) {.is-info}
abcd = [&#34;a&#34;, &#34;b&#34;, &#34;c&#34;, &#34;d&#34;] type(abcd) # &lt;class &#39;list&#39;&gt; it = iter(abcd) type(it) # &lt;class &#39;list_iterator&#39;&gt; Iterator An iterator is a value producer that yields successive values from its associated iterable object.
